title: Three key prep games to watch this week
text:
Three key prep games to watch this week Tim Johnson , Daily Herald Media 5:12 p.m. CDT October 25, 2015 Balls representing various sports 10 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Girls swimming: Wisconsin Valley Conference Meet, 4:45 p.m., Thursday, UWSP Aquatic Center, Stevens Point (Hosted by Merrill— Stevens Point Area Senior High enters the conference meet as the favorite to unseat perennial Valley champion Wausau East. SPASH capped an unbeaten run through the WVC dual meet season with a 111-56 win over Merrill on Oct. 20. D.C. Everest finished second in the dual meet standings and gave the Panthers the toughest test in the regular season with SPASH prevailing 90-80 in the opening dual meet of the conference season. 
Volleyball: WIAA sectional semifinals, 7 p.m., Thursday — Newman Catholic has not lost a set in the postseason yet and is two wins away from a return trip to the WIAA state tournament. The Cardinals face Assumption in a Division 4 matchup at Greenwood and is one of four teams in the Daily Herald Media coverage area still alive in the postseason. D.C. Everest is coming off a sweep of SPASH in a Division 1 regional title game and faces Eau Claire Memorial Thursday in Marshfield. Merrill is closing in on a return trip to state and faces West Salem in a Division 2 matchup in Stevens Point and Wittenberg-Birnamwood faces Lourdes Academy in a Division 3 game at Bay Port. 
Cross country: WIAA state meet, Noon, Saturday, The Ridges Golf Course — The D.C. Everest boys team qualified for the Division 1 field as Anthony Anderson finished first in the sectional meet in Stevens Point this past weekend. A total of 10 individuals, from Divisions 1-3, qualified for the meet as well. Marathon had four individual qualifiers, two from the girls team (Anna Buchberger, Alysha Stieber), and two from the boys squad (Xavier Lechleitner, Jordan Balz). Athens is sending two individuals to state, one girl (Autum Wickman) and tone boy (Josh Langteau). Read or Share this story: http://wdhne.ws/1N1kaDn TOP VIDEOS
